    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions achieving Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 — is mitigated by the strong output comparison results (all QoIs within 10%, E/uval < 1.96) and the standardized, tightly controlled ASTM F1717 protocol replicated across two independent laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory use of the FEA model ensemble for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU at Medium assurance level.",
